Git & Github
Lecture 11: Introduction to Git and Source Code Management
Concepts Covered
1.	What is Source Code Management (SCM)?
2.	Centralized Version Control System (CVCS) vs Distributed Version Control System (DVCS)
3.	What is Git
Explanation
Source Code Management helps developers track and manage code changes. Git is a powerful tool used for SCM.
Roman Urdu:
Source Code Managment developers ko allow karta hai ke wo code changes track, manage aur control kar saken. Git ek bohot powerful tool hai jo SCM ke liye use hota hai.
CVCS
Central repository used; example: SVN
Roman Urdu:
CVCS mein sirf aik central server hota hai jahan sara code hota hai, jaise SVN.
DVCS
Each developer has a full copy; example: Git
Roman Urdu:
DVCS mein har developer ke paas complete repository ki copy hoti hai, jaise Git.
Why Use Git?
•	Tracks changes
•	Enables collaboration
•	Open-source and distributed
Roman Urdu:
Git is liye use hota hai kyun ke:
•	har change ka record rakhta hai
•	team ke sath kaam asaan banata hai
•	open-source hai
•	distributed system hai (safe & fast)
