Lecture 12: Git Stages, Setup, and Key Commands
Concepts Covered
1.	Three Git Stages: Workspace, Staging Area, Local Repository
2.	Commands: git add, git commit, git push, git pull, git branch
3.	Setup Procedure for Git
4.	Git Terminology
5.	Advantages of Git
Concept 1: Three Git Stages
Workspace
Where you actually write or edit files.
Roman Urdu:
Workspace wo jagah hoti hai jahan hum code likhte ya edit karte hain.
Staging Area
Temporarily stores changes you want to include in the next commit.
Roman Urdu:
Staging area temporary jagah hoti hai jahan hum selected changes rakhte hain jo commit hone wale hotay hain.
Local Repository
Stores the final committed changes permanently.
Roman Urdu:
Local repository mein final commit permanently save hota hai.
Concept 2: Common Git Commands
Command — Purpose
git add — Moves changes from workspace → staging area
git commit — Saves staged changes
git push — Sends commits to GitHub
git pull — Gets changes from GitHub
git branch — Creates/switches branches
Roman Urdu:
Ye commands code ko ek stage se doosri stage tak le jane ke liye use hoti hain.
Concept 3: Git Setup
git --version
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
git config --list
Roman Urdu:
Is setup se Git ko pata chalta hai ke commit kis ne ki hai.
Concept 4: Git Terminology
Term — Explanation
Repository — Project folder
Server — Remote machine like GitHub
Workspace — Working directory
Staging Area — Temporary holding area
Commit — Snapshot of changes
Commit ID — Unique commit number
Tag — Version number (name of commit)
Branch — Separate line of development
Roman Urdu:
Ye terms Git ki basic language hain jo interview mein poochi jati hain.
Concept 5: Advantages of Git
•	Tracks history
•	Team collaboration
•	Branching & merging
•	Offline work
•	Fast & reliable
Roman Urdu:
Git fast hai, reliable hai aur DevOps ke liye perfect tool hai.
